casebody.data:
(Eighth Circuit — Cuyahoga Co., O., Circuit Court Jan. Term, 1888.) Before Judges Baldwin, Caldwell and Upson. Hart v. Murray. Arnold Green, for plaintiff in error. A. T. Brinsmade, City Solicitor, for defendant in error.

ABSTRACTS OF DECISIONS.

Final Judgment — What will not amount to — Overruling Demurrer.

Petition in error to reverse judgment of court of common pleas.

The last action of the court of common pleas was the overruling of a demurrer, and a judgment for the costs of the demurrer.

Held: There was no final judgment subject to review in error, and the petition in error was dismissed.
